<item>
            <title>[HIVE-46] derbyclient.jar and derbytools.jar should be included in hive/lib</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HIVE-46</link>
                <project id="12310843" key="HIVE">Hive</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Attempting to use the Derby ClientDriver will cause a null pointer exception because derbyclient.jar and derbytools.jar are not in lib.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;hive&amp;gt; show tables;&lt;br/&gt;
08/10/02 15:17:12 INFO hive.metastore: Trying to connect to metastore&lt;br/&gt;
with URI jdbc:derby://nyhadoop1:1527/metastore_db&lt;br/&gt;
FAILED: Error in semantic analysis: java.lang.NullPointerException&lt;br/&gt;
08/10/02 15:17:12 ERROR ql.Driver: FAILED: Error in semantic analysis:&lt;br/&gt;
java.lang.NullPointerException&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;derbyclient.jar and derbytools.jar should probably be put in the hive/lib directory. Also this type of exception could happen often with different JDBC libraries the exception should be trapped better&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;Cent OS 5 x86-64 JDK 1.6&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
